                  TraCES (ERC Advanced Grant, Grant Agreement 338756) and follow-up projects at HLCEES</ref></p><p>Sources include also <ref xml:id="grebaut" target="https://archive.org/details/supplmentaulexic0000grba">Sylvain Grébaut, Supplément au lexicon linguae aethiopicae de August Dillmann: (1865) et édition du lexique de Juste d'Urbin (1850 - 1855), Paris: Imprimerie Nationale, 1952</ref> and <ref xml:id="leslau">Wolf Leslau, Comparative Dictionary of Geʻez (Classical Ethiopic): Geʻez-English, English-Geʻez, with an Index of the Semitic Roots, Wiesbaden: Harrassowitz, 1987</ref></p></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><p>A digital edition of the Lexicon in TEI.</p><listPrefixDef><prefixDef ident="bm" matchPattern="([a-zA-Z0-9]+)" replacementPattern="https://www.zotero.org/groups/358366/ethiostudies/items/tag/bm:$1"/></listPrefixDef></encodingDesc><profileDesc><langUsage><language ident="en">English</language><language ident="fr">French</language><language ident="de">German</language><language ident="la">Latin</language><language ident="it">Italian</language><language ident="gez">Gǝʿǝz</language><language ident="grc">Ancient Greek</language><language ident="syr">Syriac</language><language ident="ar">Arabic</language><language ident="sa">Sanskrit</language><language ident="geo">Georgian</language><language ident="cop">Coptic</language><language ident="osa">Old South Arabian</language></langUsage></profileDesc><revisionDesc><change who="MK" when="2024-08-13">added gr and les </change><change who="MK" when="2024-08-13">added sub</change><change who="MK" when="2024-08-13">cerulli checked</change><change who="MK" when="2024-08-13">corrected Cerulli</change><change who="ES" when="2024-08-13">fixed bm:Cerulli19431947Etiopi</change><change who="MK" when="2024-08-29">added gr and les </change><change who="MK" when="2024-08-29">added lb</change><change who="MK" when="2024-08-29">corr</change></revisionDesc></teiHeader><text><body><div><entry xml:id="L111kumxorzo06vix2lb3jtxrti8k4ayt" n="13680"><form><foreign xml:lang="gez">ራይስ</foreign></form><sense xml:id="Tmain" xml:lang="en" source="#traces"> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">rāyǝs</t:quote></cit> <sense n="G" xml:id="TG"> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ራይስ፡</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">rāyǝs</t:quote></cit> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">prieur</t:quote></cit> (survivance de l’ancienne forme du participe actif ou nom d’agent), manque dans le <bibl><ptr target="bm:Dillmann1865Lexicon"/></bibl>. L’arabophonie <foreign xml:lang="gez">ራይስ፡</foreign> se recontre fréquemment dans les colophons et les mémoriaux des manuscrits de l’ancienne Bibliothèque du monastère éthiopien Santo-Stefano-dei-Mori (manuscrits appartenant à la Bibliothèque Vaticane). Textes et références: <foreign xml:lang="gez">በቅድመ፡... ራይስ፡ ዮሐንስ፡</foreign> Ms. <ref type="BM" target="BAVet5">BAVet5</ref>, fol. 69v; <foreign xml:lang="gez">በመዋዕለ፡ አቡነ፡ ኢሳይያስ፡ ራይስ፡</foreign> Ms. <ref type="BM" target="BAVet12">BAVet12</ref>, fol. 33v; <foreign xml:lang="gez">በራይስ፡ ዮሐንስ፡</foreign> Ms. <ref type="BM" target="BAVet25">BAVet25</ref>, fol. 1; <foreign xml:lang="gez">እንዘ፡ ራይስ፡ ጽጌ፡ ድንግል፡</foreign> Ms. <ref type="BM" target="BAVet25">BAVet25</ref>, fol. 260v. Autres exemples tirés de <bibl><ptr target="bm:Cerulli19431947Etiopi"/></bibl>: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሱቱፋን፡ ኵልነ፡ ነጋድያን፡ ሐቢረነ፡ ሠራዕነ፡ በመዋዕሊሁ፡ ለራይስ፡ ሠምረ፡ አብ።</foreign> <bibl><ptr target="bm:Cerulli19431947Etiopi"/><citedRange unit="page"> 382</citedRange></bibl>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወለዘአጽሐፈሂ፡ ለራይስ፡ ቴዎድሮስ፡ ይጽሐፍ፡ ስሞ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ውስተ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ሕይወት፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።</foreign> <bibl><ptr target="bm:Cerulli19431947Etiopi"/><citedRange unit="page"> 383</citedRange></bibl>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሠሚረነ፡ ሠራዕናሃ፡ ለማኅበረ፡ ቍስቋም፡ በራይስ፡ ተሰብከ፡ መድኅን።</foreign> <bibl><ptr target="bm:Cerulli19431947Etiopi"/><citedRange unit="page"> 384</citedRange></bibl>. <lb/>
 <bibl><ptr target="bm:Grebaut1952SuppLexicon"/><citedRange unit="page"> 158</citedRange></bibl> <lb/>
 <foreign xml:lang="gez">እረይስ፡</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">ʾǝrayǝs</t:quote></cit> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">prieur</t:quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">supérieur</t:quote></cit>. Ce mot que ne mentionne pas Dillmann {<bibl><ptr target="bm:Dillmann1865Lexicon"/></bibl>} est un arabisme provenant de ‘rāyis’. Texte et référence: <foreign xml:lang="gez">...ዘመነ፡ እረይስ፡ መቃርስ፡ በሰላመ፡ እግዚአብሔር።</foreign> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">…Au temps du prieur (rāyis) Macaire, dans la paix du Seigenur</t:quote></cit> <bibl><ptr target="bm:Cerulli19431947Etiopi"/><citedRange unit="page"> 404</citedRange></bibl> 
